\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 17-year-old Tryon Whittaker was shot to death by another youth outside of James Monroe High School in [[The Bronx]]. The boys had reportedly got into an argument and Whittaker challenged the other youth to a fight. The youth then walked away, but returned with a gun and shot Whittaker.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/10/09/nyregion/a-bronx-youth-is-shot-to-death-outside-a-school.html |title=A Bronx Youth Is Shot to Death Outside a School |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1991-10-09 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=John T. |last=McQuiston}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 14, 1991\n| [[Houston, Texas]], United States\n| ..., 16\n|\n| 1 injured\n| 18-year-old Francisco Contreras was shot four times in his feet and leg outside the cafeteria of [[Milby High School]], in [[Houston]], [[Texas]], by a 16-year-old student, who was arrested afterward. The attack was targeted.<ref>\"[https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1991_822573 Shooting at school fuels calls for more security].\" ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''. November 15, 1991.</ref>\n|-\t\n| November 25, 1991\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Jason Bentley, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| [[Thomas Jefferson High School (Brooklyn)|Thomas Jefferson High School]]. A stray bullet kills a 16-year-old student during an argument between two other teens. Shooter Jason Bentley, 14, is sentenced in 1992 to three to nine years in prison.<ref name=\"PAC\"/>\n|-\t\n| February 26, 1992\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Kahlil Sumpter, 15\n| 2 dead\n|\n| [[Thomas Jefferson High School (Brooklyn)|Thomas Jefferson High School]] was the scene of its second shooting of the school year, when a 15-year-old shot and killed two other students in a targeted attack. The shooter, Kahlil Sumpter, is sentenced in 1993 to between 6 2/3 and 20 years in prison, and is released in 1998.<ref name=\"PAC\"/>\n|-\n| May 1, 1992\n| [[Olivehurst, California]], United States\n| Eric Houston, 20\n| 4 dead\n| 10 injured\n| [[Lindhurst High School shooting]]. Armed with a pistol, 20-year-old Eric Houston took hostages at his former high school, killing four people and wounding 10. His motive was his inability to find a good job because he had failed a grade at school. He was given the [[death penalty]] for the shooting.\n|-\n| May 14, 1992\n| [[Napa, California]], United States\n| John McMahan, 14\n|\n| 2 injured\n| Armed with a [[.357 Magnum|.357-caliber]] [[pistol]], 14-year-old student John McMahan opened fire in a science classroom, wounding two.<ref name=\"Understanding lethal school violence\">{{cite book|last = Moore|first = Mark H.|author2=Carol V. Petrie |author3=Anthony A. Braga |author4=Brenda L. McLaughlin |title = Deadly Lessons: Understanding Lethal School Violence|publisher= [[National Academies Press]]|year = 2003|location = Washington, D.C.|page = 294|url = http://www.nap.edu/openbook.php?isbn=0309084121}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 11, 1992\n| [[Amarillo, Texas]], United States\n| Randy Earl Matthews, 17; ..., 15\n|\n| 6 injured\n| Six students were shot at [[Palo Duro High School]]. All survived the shooting. Police later arrested 17-year-old Randy Earl Matthews and an unidentified 15-year-old boy in connection with the shooting.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1992/09/12/us/student-wounds-6-at-high-school.html |title=Student Wounds 6 at High School |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1992-09-12 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 21, 1992\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Michael Bubb, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Damion Ennis, 15, is stabbed to death by a fellow student in a hallway of South Shore High School.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1992/09/22/nyregion/boy-15-is-fatally-stabbed-at-school-in-brooklyn.html |title=Boy, 15, Is Fatally Stabbed at School in Brooklyn |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1992-09-22 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=Robert D. |last=McFadden}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 18, 1993\n| [[Grayson, Kentucky]], United States\n| Scott Pennington, 17\n| 2 dead\n|\n| Scott Pennington shot and killed teacher Deanna McDavid and custodian Marvin Hicks after entering McDavid's classroom at East Carter High School. Pennington was later found guilty of the murders and sentenced to life imprisonment.<ref>[http://www2.indystar.com/library/factfiles/crime/school_violence/school_shootings.html School Shootings] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717151825/http://www2.indystar.com/library/factfiles/crime/school_violence/school_shootings.html |date=2011-07-17 }}. .indystar.com. Retrieved on 2010-08-16.</ref>\n|-\n| February 1, 1993\n| [[Amityville, New York]], United States\n| Shem S. McCoy, 17\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Shem S. McCoy, 17, shot two people, both cousins of his, at Amityville High School. One of those shot, Randel Artis, would die of his gunshot injuries. The three boys had apparently been engaged in a long running dispute.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/02/03/nyregion/youth-arraigned-in-killing-at-amityville-high-school.html |title=Youth Arraigned in Killing At Amityville High School |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1993-02-03 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=John T. |last=McQuiston}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 22, 1993\n| [[Los Angeles, California]], United States\n| Robert Heard, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old Robert Heard shot and killed 17-year-old Michael Shean Ensley in a corridor of [[Reseda High School]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://articles.latimes.com/1993-06-05/local/me-43640_1_reseda-high-school |title=Fatal Shooting at School Prompts Project to Spread Anti-Weapons Message \u2013 Los Angeles Times |publisher=Articles.latimes.com |date=1993-06-05 |accessdate=2009-07-03|first=Tracey|last=Kaplan}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 24, 1993\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Justin Rodriguez, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old Angel Jimenez is stabbed to death by another 15-year-old student in a hallway of Junior High School 25. The stabbing was sparked by a dispute between the two boys over who owned a pair of sunglasses.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/02/25/nyregion/15-year-old-dies-in-attack-in-school-hall.html |title=15-Year-Old Dies in Attack In School Hall |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1993-02-25 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |first=Sam |last=Dillon}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 18, 1993\n| [[Harlem, Georgia]], United States\n| Edward Bryant Gillom, 15\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Edward Bryant Gillom, a freshman at Harlem High School, shot two fellow students, killing 15-year-old Ronrecas Gibson.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://chat.augustachronicle.com/stories/1999/11/28/met_276184.shtml |title=A look at the 20th century: 1993 |publisher=Chat.augustachronicle.com |date=1999-11-28 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120707130426/http://chat.augustachronicle.com/stories/1999/11/28/met_276184.shtml |archive-date=2012-07-07 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| April 15, 1993\n| [[Acushnet, Massachusetts]], United States\n| David Taber, 44\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 44-year-old David Taber invades Ford Middle School and takes three hostages. He later shoots and kills school nurse Carol Day. He is found not guilty of the murder by reason of insanity.<ref name=\"PAC\"/>\n|-\n| May 24, 1993\n| [[Pennsburg, Pennsylvania]], United States\n| Jason Smith, 15\n| 1 dead\n| \n| [[Upper Perkiomen High School]] student, 15-year-old, Jason Smith shoots and kills another student who had bullied him. He is sentenced to between 12 and 25 years in prison.<ref name=\"PAC\"/><ref>{{cite web | url=http://articles.philly.com/1993-10-15/news/25936622_1_shot-classmate-jason-michael-smith-michael-swann | title=Prison Term For Murder At School Jason Michael Smith Received 12 1/2 To 25 Years For Shooting A Classmate At Upper Perkiomen High School In May. |publisher=philly.com | date=October 15, 1993 | accessdate=December 11, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 17, 1993\n| [[Sheridan, Wyoming]], United States\n| Kevin Newman, 29\n| 1 dead\n| 4 injured\n| 4 students in a physical education class were wounded at Central Middle School in Sheridan, Wyoming, when 29-year-old Kevin Newman fired at them with a handgun while the class was doing lessons outdoors. He then committed suicide by shooting himself in the head. A suicide note found in Newman's motel room revealed that he was unhappy with his life, and thought of himself as an evil person.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=lm0xAAAAIBAJ&sjid=VwMEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6650,4748310&dq= Gunman attacks school, kills himself], ''[[Toledo Blade]]'' (September 18, 1993)</ref><ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=bR0PAAAAIBAJ&sjid=4oQDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5130,5790941&dq= Suicide note says Wyoming gunman \"evil\"], ''[[The Deseret News]]'' (September 27, 1993)</ref>\n|-\n| September 17, 1993\n| [[Darien, Illinois]], United States\n| Phillip Powell, 15\n| 1 dead\n| \n| 15-year-old Phillip Powell killed 17-year-old Barrett Modisette in Hinsdale South High School\u2019s parking lot. Powell was a self-described gang member, who shot Barrett because Barrett was protecting his younger brother from Powell's verbal bullying. Powell was tried as an adult and was sentenced to 37 years in prison in 1994.<ref>[http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1994-07-27/news/9407270381_1_student-s-death-gang-violence-sentenced 16-year-old Killer Gets 37 Years], \u2018\u2019[[Chicago Tribune]]\u2019\u2019 (July 27, 1994)</ref>\n|-\n| October 6, 1993\n| [[Hausleiten]], Austria\n| ..., 13\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| A 13-year-old student, waiting at the entrance of the [[Hauptschule]] in Hausleiten, shot and wounded the principal of the school with a rifle before committing suicide. The student was caught smoking the day before and the principal told the boy he had to inform his parents about it.<ref>[http://diepresse.com/home/panorama/oesterreich/310346/index.do?direct=310340&_vl_backlink=/home/panorama/index.do&selChannel= Gewehr, Revolver, Messer im Klassenzimmer], ''[[Die Presse]]'' (June 13, 2007)</ref>\n|-\n| December 1, 1993\n| [[Wauwatosa, Wisconsin]], United States\n| Leonard McDowell, 21\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Leonard McDowell, a 21-year-old former student at [[Wauwatosa West High School]], shot Associate Principal Dale Breitlow three times with a .44-cal. Taurus revolver in a second-floor hallway. McDowell was found guilty of the murder and sane at the time of the shooting. His life sentence was upheld by the state Court of Appeals in April, 1997.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.jsonline.com/story/index.aspx?id=506749|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071014115039/http://www.jsonline.com/story/index.aspx?id=506749|url-status=dead|title=Milwaukee - home|archivedate=October 14, 2007}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 17, 1993\n| [[Chelsea, Michigan]], United States\n| Stephen Leith\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| Steve Leith, a science teacher at [[Chelsea High School (Michigan)|Chelsea High School]], walked into a staff meeting being held at the school and shot and killed the district superintendent, and also wounded the school principal and a teacher. Leith was then arrested by police.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/12/17/us/police-arrest-a-teacher-in-school-shootings.html |title=Police Arrest a Teacher in School Shootings |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1993-12-17 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=pOsVAAAAIBAJ&sjid=5hQEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6924,418870&dq=chelsea+michigan+school&hl=en |title=Teacher arrested in school shootings |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1993-12-17 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 31, 1994\n| [[Seattle, Washington]], United States\n| Darrell Cloud, 24\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 24-year-old Darrell Cloud entered Whitman Middle School and shot his former teacher, 45-year-old Neal Summers, to death. Cloud would serve nine years in prison for the murder. The motive for the shooting was sexual abuse that was alleged to have been perpetrated by Summers against Cloud since Cloud was 13 years old.<ref>{{cite news|last=Shaw |first=Linda |url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/localnews/2002162113_cloud26m.html |title=Abuse victim who killed teacher settles with district |publisher=Seattletimes.nwsource.com |date=2005-01-27 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 1, 1994\n| [[Simi Valley, California]], United States\n| Chad Patrick Hubbard, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 14-year old Phillip Hernandez killed his bully, also 14-year-old Chad Patrick Hubbard, by stabbing him in the heart with a pocket knife.<ref>http://www.columbine-angels.com/School_Violence_1993-1994.htm</ref><ref>https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1994-07-30-me-21582-story.html</ref><ref>https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1994-07-30-me-21582-story.html</ref>\n|-\n| March 1, 1994\n| [[Boonville, Missouri]], United States\n| Dante D. Hayes, 33\n| 2 dead\n| \n| Dante D. Hayes, 33, a hunter and ex-convict, shot and killed Richard Vancena, 58, a cafeteria manager, and Robin Michelle Coleman, 33, a cook, in the mess hall of [[Kemper Military School]]. He was drunk and looking for his wife Anna Hayes with whom he had a fight the night before. No students were harmed.<ref>{{cite news|author=Associated Press |url=http://www.deseretnews.com/article/339317/GUNMAN-KILLS-2-AT-MISSOURI-MILITARY-SCHOOL.html?pg=all |title=GUNMAN KILLS 2 AT MISSOURI MILITARY SCHOOL |newspaper=Deseret News |date=1994-03-02 |accessdate=2014-06-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 23, 1994\n| [[Seattle, Washington]], United States\n| Brian Ronquillo,\nCesar Sarausad II, 19\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| A gang-related drive-by shooting outside Ballard High School resulted in the death of 16-year-old student Melissa Fernandes and the wounding of 17-year-old student Brent Mason. Police later arrested two men in connection with the shooting.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://komonews.com/news/local/court-may-reinstate-conviction-in-deadly-seattle-school-shooting |title=Court may reinstate conviction in deadly Seattle school shooting |publisher=Komonews.com |date=2008-11-21 |accessdate=2016-07-22}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 25, 1994\n| [[Cherokee County, Georgia]], United States\n| Brian Head, 15\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old Brian Head shot and killed himself during his economics class at [[Etowah High School (Georgia)|Etowah High School]]. Head had been a longtime target for bullies because of his weight and thick glasses. His father, Bill, subsequently successfully lobbied for a law that criminalized bullying and required schools to alert parents of bullied children.\n|-\n| March 28, 1994\n| [[Acklam, Middlesbrough]], United Kingdom\n| Stephen Wilkinson, 29\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| Stephen Wilkinson burst into a mathematics classroom at [[Hall Garth Community Arts College]] and stabbed three children, including 12-year-old Nikki Conroy, who later died from her injuries.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/talks-to-comfort-pupils-after-killing-counselling-starts-for-children-still-in-shock-after-classroom-stabbing-malcolm-pithers-reports-1432491.html |title=Talks to comfort pupils after killing: Counselling starts for children still in shock after classroom stabbing |publisher=Independent.co.uk |date=1994-03-30 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |location=London |first=Malcolm |last=Pithers}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 26, 1994\n| [[Union, Kentucky]], United States\n| [[Clay Shrout]], 17\n| 4 dead\n|\n| Clay Shrout kills his mother, father, and two younger sisters before embarking a [[hostage situation]] in a [[trigonometry]] classroom. He's now serving life in prison.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enquirer.com/editions/2004/05/25/loc_shrout25prison.html |title=Clay Shrout reported of prison behavioral problems |publisher=Enquirer.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| June 17, 1994\n| [[Holywood, Northern Ireland]], United Kingdom\n| [[Sullivan Upper School#The 1994 attack|Garnet Bell]], 46\n|\n| 6 injured\n| A former pupil bearing a grudge entered an assembly hall 