hool Shooting |url= https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F07E2DE1F38F93BA25752C0A9649C8B63 |work= [[The New York Times]] |date= 2002-01-18 |accessdate=2008-02-20 }}</ref> In February 2003, Rodriguez was sentenced to 10 years in prison on charges of assault and attempted assault.<ref>{{cite news |author=Saulny, Susan |title= New York: Manhattan: Teenager Sentenced In School Shootings |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2003/02/21/nyregion/metro-briefing-new-york-manhattan-teenager-sentenced-in-school-shootings.html |work= [[The New York Times]] |date= February 21, 2003 |accessdate= August 4, 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n| February 19, 2002\n| [[Freising]], Germany\n| Adam Labus, 22\n| 4 dead\n| 1 injured\n| 22-year-old Adam Labus killed his former boss and a worker in [[Eching, Freising|Eching]], before driving to his former school in Freising where he shot and killed the principal and injured another teacher. He then committed suicide.<ref>[http://www.spiegel.de/spiegel/print/d-21542114.html?name=Die+Rache+des+kleinen+Rambo Die Rache des kleinen Rambo], ''[[Der Spiegel]]'' (9/2002)</ref>\n|-\n| April 26, 2002\n| [[Erfurt]], [[Thuringia]], Germany\n| [[Robert Steinh\u00e4user]], 19\n| 17 dead\n| 7 injured\n| [[Erfurt massacre]]. 19-year-old Robert Steinh\u00e4user, who was permanently expelled from school in October 2001, entered the [[Gutenberg-Gymnasium Erfurt|Gutenberg-Gymnasium]] in Erfurt and shot and killed 13 teachers, two students and a police officer. He also wounded seven other people. He then committed suicide.\n|-\n| April 30, 2002\n| [[Vlasenica]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n| Dragoslav Petkovic, 17\n| 2 dead\n| 1 injured\n| 17-year-old Dragoslav Petkovic shot and killed his history teacher outside the school. He then made his way into the building where he shot and seriously injured another teacher. Petkovic then committed suicide inside the classroom with thirty students present.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bosnia Student Kills Teacher and Himself|url=https://ww