2 gauge]] [[shotgun]] and opened fire. A 16-year-old male student, identified as Bowe Cleveland, was shot in the chest and critically wounded. Another student was shot at, but was not hit. The classroom teacher, Ryan Heber, convinced him to drop his weapon, and the gunman followed his order and was later arrested. Additionally, Heber suffered a minor wound from being grazed by a shotgun [[Lead shot|pellet]] during the ordeal. The gunman is suspected to be a 16-year-old student of the school, Bryan Oliver. Cleveland and the other student that was shot at are both believed to be intended targets of the gunman. On January 14, Oliver was charged with two counts of attempted murder and assault with a firearm.<ref>[http://www.wptv.com/dpp/news/national/taft-high-school-shooting-update-reports-indicate-at-least-2-people-shot-in-california-high-school Taft High School shooting update: Reports indicate at least 1 person shot in California high school] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130112232551/http://www.wptv.com/dpp/news/national/taft-high-school-shooting-update-reports-indicate-at-least-2-people-shot-in-california-high-school |date=2013-01-12 }} Retrieved January 10, 2013</ref><ref name=usatoday>{{cite news|last=Winter|first=Michael|author2=Stanglin, Doug |title=Calif. teen with shotgun wounds classmate in school|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2013/01/10/taft-california-shooting-high-school/1823539/|work=[[USA Today]]|publisher=January 10, 2013|accessdate=January 10, 2013|date=January 10, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 12, 2013\n| [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]], United States\n| Unknown suspect\n| \n| 1 injured\n| A 16-year-old boy was shot in a field across the school campus after a basketball game was held at [[Osborn High School]]. He was hospitalized in serious condition.<ref name=detroitcbslocal>{{cite web|title=Teen Shot After High School Basketball Game|url=http://detroit.cbslocal.com/2013/01/12/teen-shot-after-high-school-basketball-game/|w