 Taub Hospital]]. The suspect was then placed in the Harris County Juvenile Probation Department. It was reported that the possible motive was the victim making an insulting comment about the suspect's clothing.<ref>Markley, Melanie. \"[https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1996_1371129 Studying our Schools: Challenges / Safety matters: Issue is No. 1 concern with parents].\" ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''. October 13, 1996.</ref><ref>Hanson, Eric. \"[https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1990_731137 Teen fatally stabbed in classroom / Victim pays for insult to girl's shorts with life].\" ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''. September 22, 1990.</ref>\n|-\n| April 10, 1991\n| [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]], United Kingdom\n| Barbara Glover, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 16-year-old Diane Watson is stabbed to death by 16-year-old Barbara Glover at Whitehill Secondary School in the Dennistoun area of Glasgow.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/616759.stm|work=BBC News|title=Parents protest at killer's parole bid|date=January 24, 2000|accessdate=May 8, 2010}}</ref> Both Watson and Glover were students at the school.<ref>{{cite web|author=The Committee Office, House of Commons |url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200203/cmselect/cmcumeds/458/458w125.htm |title=Appendix 124 Memorandum submitted by Margaret and James Watson |publisher=Publications.parliament.uk |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 23, 1991\n| [[Compton, California]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A teenager aimed and fired a handgun at a security guard who had chased him and three friends off the grounds of Ralph J. Bunche Middle School. However, instead of hitting his intended target, the bullet struck 11-year-old bystander Alejandro Vargas, a student at the school, killing him.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://articles.latimes.com/1991-04-24/local/me-536_1_security-guard |title=Shot Fired at Guard Kills Boy at School |publisher=Articles.latimes.com |date=1991-09-19 |accessdate