 week for disorderly conduct entered the school through the back door and fired three shots in the cafeteria, with two hitting the ceiling and one entering the wall of a classroom. The suspect left the firearm and fled, but was later apprehended by a security officer and a school administrator. The shooter, 15-year-old Keith Elliott, was charged as an adult with gun violations, armed burglary and assault.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wavy.com/dpp/news/local_news/high-school-suspect-tried-as-adult |title=HS shooting suspect tried as adult |publisher=Wavy.com |date=2010-05-17 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100523234915/http://www.wavy.com/dpp/news/local_news/high-school-suspect-tried-as-adult |archivedate=2010-05-23 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.dailypress.com/news/southside/dp-now-portsmouth-school-gun.a28,0,7755510.story Student charged after shots fired at Portsmouth high school]. Daily Press (2010-04-28). Retrieved on 2010-08-16.</ref>\n|-\n| June 10, 2010\n| [[Binghamton, New York|Binghamton]],<br>[[New York (state)|New York]],<br>United States\n|\n|\n| 20 or more injured\n| A brawl broke out among the students of Binghamton High School. It started as a food fight-prank in the cafeteria, then radiated out into the streets. Some police officers and school personnel suffered minor injuries, and at least one school administrator suffered more serious injuries. Over 100 students then gathered at Oak and Main streets and the situation rapidly degraded. Police broke up the incident. The skirmishes resulted in at least 9 students being arrested and charged with disorderly conduct, resisting arrest, and/or assault in the 2nd degree. The school was put on lockdown for the rest of the day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wivb.com/dpp/news/new_york/school-food-fight-injures-principals |title=School food fight injures principals |publisher=Wivb.com |date=2010-06-11 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| July 2, 2010\n| [[Heredia, 