ck |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/08/12/michael-phelps-indiana-te_0_n_925919.html |title=Michael Phelps, Indiana Teen, Sentenced To 35 Years In Prison For School Shooting |work=Huffington Post |date=August 12, 2011 |accessdate=December 27, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 30, 2011\n| [[Houston, Texas|Houston]],<br>[[Texas]],<br>United States\n| 2 unknown gunman \n| 1 dead\n| 5 injured\n| An 18-year-old man died and five other people were injured when two people opened fire during a football game at [[Worthing High School (Houston, Texas)|Worthing High School]] in Houston. Police suspected that the shooting was gang-related.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/8301-504083_162-20049227-504083.html|title=1 dead in Worthing High School shooting, police say it was possibly gang-related|website=cbsnews.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 23, 2011\n| [[Pearl City, Hawaii]], United States\n| Student, 14\n|\n| 1 injured\n| A 14-year-old student is accused of firing a handgun on the campus of Highlands Intermediate School, in a targeted attack, wounding one student. The gunman was arrested on suspicion of attempted murder. Two other suspects were arrested in connection with the shooting.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.civilbeat.com/posts/2011/06/15/11772-a-third-hawaii-teen-arrested-in-school-shooting/|work=Honolulu Civil Beat | title=A Third Hawaii Teen Arrested In School Shooting | date=June 15, 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| July 18, 2011\n| [[Orotina]], [[Costa Rica]]\n| Suspect, 17\n| 2 dead\n| \n| 17-year-old Juan Pablo Salazar Calder\u00f3n was gunned down at his desk at the Colegio T\u00e9cnico Profesional Ricardo Castro Beer in Orotina. The killer, just short of 18 years old himself, shot himself in the head after killing Salazar, and was left in critical condition. The shooter later died of his injuries in hospital.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.amcostarica.com/011113.htm | title=Analysis of school shooting fails to suggest remedies | date=January 11, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| Augus